## 💻 DEVELOPMENT PRACTICES

### Code File Naming Standards (SDLC 4.9.1)
```yaml
Python Files (.py):
  Convention: snake_case (lowercase_with_underscores)
  Maximum Length: 50 characters (excluding .py extension)
  Examples:
    ✅ user_service.py
    ✅ customer_serializers.py
    ✅ bcc_generator.py
    ❌ UserService.py (PascalCase - wrong)
    ❌ a502ce0d23a7_seed_data_realistic_mtc_nqh_examples.py (67 chars - too long)

TypeScript/JavaScript Files (.ts, .tsx, .js, .jsx):
  Convention: camelCase for files, PascalCase for React components
  Maximum Length: 50 characters (excluding extension)
  Examples:
    ✅ userService.ts
    ✅ UserProfile.tsx (component)
    ❌ user_service.ts (snake_case - wrong)

Alembic Migrations:
  Convention: {revision}_{description}.py
  Maximum Length: 60 characters (excluding .py extension)
  Examples:
    ✅ 001_create_users.py
    ✅ a502ce0d_seed_mtc_data.py
    ❌ a502ce0d23a7_seed_data_realistic_mtc_nqh_examples.py (too long)

Reference: 08-Documentation-Standards/SDLC-Code-File-Naming-Standards.md
```

### Code Structure (Battle-Tested)
